        public void initSetup()
        This method is called at the start of the game. It's purpose is to initialize 4 different patternCards and a private objective for each player and send them so that they can pick one

        idPlayer - id that represents the player view

      • setDieInPatternCardFromDiceArena

        public void setDieInPatternCardFromDiceArena(int idPlayer,
                                             int idDie,
                                             int x,
                                             int y,
                                             boolean ignoreAdjacency,
                                             int idToolCard)
        This method gives the opportunity to the controller to set a die in the chosen patternCard of the player. It is used both during a normal positioning of a die but it is also used by many tool cards. It checks everything before placing the die and in case something goes wrong, it generates a notify to tell the player what went wrong
        Parameters:
        idPlayer - player id that made the set of the die in the patternCard
        idDie - die id chosen by the player
        x - abscissa chosen by the player
        y - ordinate chosen by the player
        ignoreAdjacency - it is used for the tool card number 9 so that you can place a die away from other dice
        idToolCard - in case you are using this method with a tool card. It is needed to update tool card cost and the player's number of tokens

      • endTurn

        public void endTurn(PlayerMessageEndTurn playerMessageEndTurn)
        Method to create the end of a turn. In case it was the last turn of the round, it's gonna start a new round and put the dice left on the draft pool in the round finished which is gonna be sent to the player. It then sends the player of this game a ModelChangedMessageRefresh which contains the player id who will be playing now. It also stops the current timer and stars a new one. It resets to false the setHasSetDieThisTurn and setHasUsedToolCardThisTurn of the player who is about to start his turn If it is the last turn, it changes the game phase to ENDGAME
        Parameters:
        playerMessageEndTurn - it's the message generated by the player; it contains the id that represents the player who just finished its turn

      • timesUp

        public void timesUp()
        This method is called by the thread timer only if the player doesn't end the turn before the 90 seconds timer ends. If it happens during the choosing of the pattern card, it gives the player the first available pattern card. If it happens during the GAMEPHASE, it invokes the method endTurn() and sends a message to the current player playing saying that he run out of time and he is now considered AFK.

      • timeIsRunningOut

        public void timeIsRunningOut()
        Sends a message to the player playing informing him that in 15 minutes his round will end and he will be set suspended

      • checkToolCard

        public boolean checkToolCard(int idPlayer,
                             int idToolCard)
        checkToolCard controls if the tool card chosen by the player is actually "on the table" and whether or not the player has used a tool card this turn or has not enough tokens. In case of negative response, it generates a error message that is gonna be sent to the player that was trying to use the tool card.
        Parameters:
        idPlayer - player id that tried to use the tool card
        idToolCard - tool card id chosen by the player
        Returns:
        true if the player can actually use the tool card, false otherwise

      • incrementOrDecrementDieValue

        public void incrementOrDecrementDieValue(int idPlayer,
                                         int idDie,
                                         int changeValue,
                                         int idToolCard)
        this method is invoked when the player tries to use tool card number 1. it checks whether or not die id is acceptable and if the player is trying to turn a 6 into a 1 or a 1 into a six. In case something goes wrong, it generates a error message, otherwise it changes the value of the die by one and then sends the updated draft pool to all the players in this game. It also sets that the player has used a tool card this turn and it removes the tokens from the player equal to the cost of the tool card.
        Parameters:
        idPlayer - player id using this tool card
        idDie - die id that the player wants to change
        changeValue - 0 if the player want to decrease the value of the die, 1 if the player wants to increase the value of the die
        idToolCard - tool card id necessary to update the player's tokens and the tool card cost

      • moveDieInsidePatternCard

        public void moveDieInsidePatternCard(int idPlayer,
                                     java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> positions,
                                     boolean ignoreValueConstraint,
                                     boolean ignoreColorConstraint,
                                     int idToolCard)
        This method is used by all the tool card that want to move only one die inside a pattern card. if the moves is fine, it updates the tool card cost and the player's tokens. In case performMoveDieInsidePatternCard doesn't end well and it catches a PatternCardMoveFailedException, there is no need to do anything because the player has been notified of his mistake by setDieInPatternCard.
        Parameters:
        idPlayer - player id that used the tool card
        positions - list of integer containing the starting and final position of the die movement, both characterized by a abscissa and a ordinate
        ignoreValueConstraint - needed for tool card number 3 so that you can ignore value constraints on the cell
        ignoreColorConstraint - needed for tool card number 2 so that you can ignore color constraints on the cell
        idToolCard - tool card id necessary to update tool card cost and player's tokens

      • moveTwoDiceInsidePatternCard

        public void moveTwoDiceInsidePatternCard(int idPlayer,
                                         java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> positions1,
                                         java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> positions2,
                                         int idToolCard)
        This method is needed when you need to make two dice movements inside a pattern card. The way it works is really simple: it performs the first movement: if there is a problem, the movement doesn't go trough and the me thod ends; if it does go through, it performs the second movement: if the is no problem, it updates the tool card cost and the player's tokens. If the second movements doesn't go trough, the first movement is reversed and to make sure it goes trough, both ignoreValueConstraint and ignoreColorConstraint are set to true
        Parameters:
        idPlayer - player id using the tool card
        positions1 - positions relative to the firm movement: list of integer containing the starting and final position of the die movement, both characterized by a abscissa and a ordinate
        positions2 - positions relative to the second movement: list of integer containing the starting and final position of the die movement, both characterized by a abscissa and a ordinate
        idToolCard - tool card id necessary to update tool card cost and player's tokens

        public void turnDieAround(int idPlayer,

        This method is needed for tool card number 10. It turn around the die. It check whether or not the die id is accepted and in case it's not, it send a notify with ModelChangedMessageMoveFailed as parameter.
        Parameters:

        idDie - die id that the player want to turn around
        idToolCard - tool card id needed to update tool card cost and player's tokens

      • rollDieAgain

        public void rollDieAgain(int idPlayer,
                         int idDie,
                         int idToolCard)
        Method needed for tool card 6. First it checks whether or not idDie is accepted for the draft pool. After that it rolls the die again and creates ModelChangedMessageNewEvent telling the player using the tool card the new value of the die
        Parameters:
        idPlayer - player id using the tool card
        idDie - die id that the player want to roll again
        idToolCard - tool card id needed to update tool card cost and player's tokens

      • swapDieAmongRoundTrackAndDiceArena

        public void swapDieAmongRoundTrackAndDiceArena(int idPlayer,
                                               int dieIdInRoundTrack,
                                               int idRound,
                                               int dieIdInDiceArena,
                                               int idToolCard)
        Method needed for tool card 5. The method first checks if the die di in draft pool is present or not. After that the method gets the actualIdDie (the player will have selected a die id that goes from 0 to 8, while the actual die id can go from 0 to 89) and it puts it in the round selected by the player while it removes the die id in round track selected by the player. If the die is not present in the round track, it catches a DieNotPresentException. After that the method swaps the die in the draft pool: if everything goes fine, the tool card cost and the player tokens gets updated and the method ends. If the die id in dice arena chosen by the player does not exist, the method catches another DieNotPresentException and swaps back the dice in the round track. Whenever it catches and exception, the method sends a notify with a ModelChangedMessageMoveFailed to the player currently playing explaining what went wrong
        Parameters:
        idPlayer - player id that wants to perform the swap
        dieIdInRoundTrack - die id selected by the player on the roundTrack
        idRound - round it selected by the player where the dieIdInRoundTrack should be present
        dieIdInDiceArena - die id selected by the player in the draft pool
        idToolCard - tool card id needed to update tool card cost and player's tokens

      • swapDieWithDieFromDiceBag

        public java.lang.Integer swapDieWithDieFromDiceBag(int idPlayer,
                                                   int idDie)
        This methos serves for tool card number 11. This method removes a die from the draft pool and it sets it back to unrolled and extract a new die, sending the player a ModelChangedMessageNewEvent containing the color of the new die extracted. If the die id choses by the player is not acceptable, the method notifies the player with a ModelChangedMessageMoveFailed
        Parameters:
        idPlayer - player id choosing the die
        idDie - die id chosen by the player to remove from the draft pool
        Returns:
        idNewDie that contains the id of the new die extracted from the dice bag. If die id chosen by the player was not acceptable, it return -1 so that the following steps of the tool card are not executed

                           int value)
        This method purpose is to give the value chosen by the player to the new die extracted from the dice bag during tool card number 11.
        Parameters:

        actualIdDie - actual die id (the one that goes from 0 to 89)
        value - value (from 1 to 6) chosen by the player to assign to the die extracted

      • setPlayerSuspended

        public void setPlayerSuspended(int idPlayer,
                               boolean afk)
        This method puts a certain player suspended or un-suspended, whether he didn't finish his turn or whether he disconnected. If the number of players remaining is only 1, it finishes the game.

        Parameters:
